      <description>

&lt;h3 id=&#34;press&#34;&gt;Press&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;http://www.russellsage.org/news/income-inequality-and-class-divides-parental-investments&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;Russell Sage Foundation: &amp;ldquo;Income Inequality and Class Divides in Parental Investments&amp;rdquo;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;

&lt;li&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.coloradoan.com/story/news/2018/05/31/colorado-state-university-research-shows-education-spending-gap/661289002/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;&lt;em&gt;Coloradoan&lt;/em&gt;: &amp;ldquo;Parent spending on children&amp;rsquo;s education is &amp;lsquo;an arms race,&amp;rsquo; and poorer families are falling farther behind&amp;rdquo;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;

&lt;li&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.usnews.com/news/education-news/articles/2018-05-28/income-inequality-exacerbates-the-achievement-gap&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;&lt;em&gt;US News&lt;/em&gt;: &amp;ldquo;The Growing Achievement Gap&amp;rdquo;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;

&lt;li&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://ifstudies.org/blog/rising-income-inequality-widens-the-class-divide-in-parenting-practices-an-interview-with-orestes-pat-hastings&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;Institute for Family Studies: &amp;ldquo;Rising Income Inequality Widens the Class Divide in Parenting Practices: An Interview with Orestes Pat Hastings&amp;rdquo;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;

&lt;li&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.educationdive.com/news/income-inequality-drives-summer-slide-even-among-youngest-students/524639/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;Education Dive: &amp;ldquo;Income inequality drives summer slide, even among youngest students&amp;rdquo;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;

&lt;li&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.chalkbeat.org/posts/us/2018/05/30/the-shadow-education-system-how-wealthier-students-benefit-from-art-music-and-theater-over-the-summer-while-poor-kids-miss-out/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;Chalkbeat: &amp;ldquo;The ‘shadow education system’: How wealthier students benefit from art, music, and theater over the summer while poor kids miss out&amp;rdquo;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;

&lt;li&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://libarts.source.colostate.edu/study-gap-between-what-the-rich-and-poor-spend-on-their-kids-is-widening/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;CSU SOURCE: &amp;ldquo;Gap between what the rich and poor spend on their kids is widening&amp;rdquo; &lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;

&lt;li&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;http://www.asanet.org/news-events/asa-news/income-inequality-changing-how-parents-invest-their-kids-widening-class-divides-us&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;American Sociological Association: &amp;ldquo;Income inequality is changing how parents invest in their kids, widening class divides in the U.S.&amp;rdquo;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
